## M4 — Player position pills (planned)

Each rendered player (starter on pitch + alternate in stack + "Other subs" pill) shows: `[POSITION] Name`.

- Pill = small uppercase code in a muted background (`bg-surface-md`, `text-fg-low`, `tracking-widest`, `font-size: 7px`, `padding: 2px 4px`, `border-radius: 3px`).
- Multi-position primary-pick rule: **first code in `positions[]`** (the array preserves the order the player chose in `PositionMultiSelect`, so this IS effectively the player-pinned primary).
- Empty `positions[]` → no pill.

This makes it visually obvious when a CM player is filling an LM slot (pill says CM, slot dot is at the LM coordinate with the LM slot label).

