## M3 — Subs as depth-chart alternates shipped

- New `assignAlternatesToSlots(ballType, formation, subs)` — per-sub greedy single-listing: first primary-eligible slot in slot order, else first fallback-eligible slot, else `noFitOverflow`.
- `<SlotColumn>` (renamed from `<SlotDot>`) renders `starter + alternates` stacked vertically at each pitch coordinate.
- Per-slot cap: `MAX_ALTERNATES_PER_SLOT = 3`. Anything beyond plus `noFitOverflow` lands in the "Other subs" pill row below the pitch.
- The "Subs (N)" row of v1.83.1 is gone — only OTHER subs (truncated or no-fit) show below the pitch.

### Duplicate-listing decision

Per M3 plan: implemented **'show under primary slot only'** (single-listing). Rationale: pitch is dense, multi-position players (CB-fallback for LB/RB/DM, CM-fallback for LM/RM/CAM/DM) would clutter every slot. The depth-chart frame stays legible.

### Layout density on mobile (360px viewport)

- Pitch container: 3:4 aspect ratio → ~360×480px.
- Each slot column max-width 78px (constrains long names + truncates with `truncate`).
- Alternate stack: 7px font + 1px row gap → ~9px per row → 3 rows ≈ 27px tall (~5.6% pitch height).
- The CB row of a 4-3-3 has 4 slot columns at x = {0.15, 0.38, 0.62, 0.85}: at 360px, columns sit at {54, 137, 223, 306} — adjacent columns spaced ≥83px, room for the 78px max-width without horizontal collision. Verified by simple math; visual smoke deferred to user during manual review.

